<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-248-501  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 248 501.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  Jan 2 1989 n229 p28(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New MCCA unit. (Mobile Communications Corporation of America)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wilde, Candee.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Mobile Communications Corp of America (MMCA) appoints Thomas G.andO;Barksdale as president and COO of Mobile TelecommunicationsTechnologies Corp, a new, wholly owned subsidiary of the company.andO;The creation of Mobile Telecommunications is the result of amerger agreement under which Atlanta-based Bell-South Corp willacquire MMCA's local and regional paging operations, and cellularradio telephone interests.andP;  The subsidiary will consist ofsatellite paging, voice-mail and telephone-answering services, andMMCA's air-to-ground, marine communication and satellitecommunication businesses.andP;  The merger was completed under twoconditions: that the US District Court for the District ofColumbia waives interLATA (local access and transport area)stipulations for BellSouth, and that the Securities and ExchangeCommission declare Mobile Telecom's stock registration statementeffective.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Mobile Communications Corporation of America (officials andemployees)BellSouth Corp. (acquisitions and mergers).andO;Topic:     MergerNew AppointmentExecutive.andO;Feature:   illustrationportrait.andO;Caption:   Thomas G. Barksdale. (portrait)Person:    Barksdale, Thomas G. (selection and appointment).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>